             and another.</p>
               <p>HARRIET YARNOLD. I am shopwoman to Messrs. 
               <persName id="t18310630-296-person2123">
                  James 
                  Tavener
               <interp inst="t18310630-296-person2123" type="surname" value="Tavener"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-296-person2123" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-296-person2123" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             and Ely Kimpton, of <placeName id="t18310630-296-crimeloc1551">Oxford-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310630-296-crimeloc1551" type="placeName" value="Oxford-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310630-296-crimeloc1551" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310630-296-off1549 t18310630-296-crimeloc1551"></join>. On the 4th of June the prisoner brought a piece of black silk to the shop, and said Mr. Foster would be obliged by our giving him a pattern to match it as near as we could; I gave him one - he returned in about ten minutes, and said Mr. Foster would be obliged to us to let him have the piece; I gave it him - it was twelve yards and a quarter; he brought that back, and said Mr. Foster wanted thirty<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183106300135"></xptr>yards at least; Mr. Tavener then gave him a piece of sixty-seven yards, worth about 10l. - he left the other, and went away.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. STURGEON. Q.Had you known him before? A. No - I am sure he is the man.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310630-296-person2124">
                  JAMES 
                  TAVENER
               <interp inst="t18310630-296-person2124" type="surname" value="TAVENER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-296-person2124" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-296-person2124" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I let the prisoner have the silk, and in consequence of suspicion, I watched him into Mr. Foster's - I then returned, and sent Burton to Mr. Foster's.</p>
               <p>JOHN BURTON. I am in the prosecutors' employ. I went to Foster's, and as I went in I met the prisoner coming out - I followed him to Rathbone-place; he then began running, and went on to Greek-street - I overtook him there, and asked if he had not brought a piece of silk from Mr. Wild's, in Rathbone-place; he said Yes, and he was going to take it to a customer - I went with him; he called in Gower-street, in Bedford-square, and Tavistocksquare - I then said he should not go further till he told me where the customer lived; he said at No. 36, Guildford-street - he went there; the person he inquired for was not at home - he came back to Wild's, in Rathbone-place, and they said they knew nothing of him; he then said a person in a surtout coat, who stood at their door, gave it to him.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Did he attempt to run away? A. No.</p>
               <p>ROBERT MILLARD. On the 4th of June the prisoner came into Mr. Foster's with a piece of silk, and said he should want two pieces to match it for Mr. Wild; I gave him a pattern - he went out; Burton came in: I told him what had passed - the prisoner was not in Mr. Foster's service, and was not sent from our shop for the silk.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. How many persons have you? A. One more shopman.</p>
               <p>ROBERT KNOWLES. I am a Police-constable. On the 4th of June I was fetched to Mr. Wild's - Burton charged the prisoner with taking the roll of silk from Mr. Tavener- he said a young man at Wild's door sent him to Tavener's for it.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18310630-296-verdict1552" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310630-296-verdict1552" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 26. - <rs id="t18310630-296-punish1553" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310630-296-punish1553" type="punishmentCategory" value="imprison"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310630-296-defend2120 t18310630-296-punish1553"></join>
               Confined Three Months
            </rs>.</p>
